<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
I just thought this was hysterical.  Doubt it's worth fixing. <p>
Apparently a staircase got teleported... I seem to recall that there is a trap that will do that, or maybe a scroll.  Anyway, it was embedded in the rock up in the upper right hand corner of the dungeon.  Only way I could tell it was there was that this is a Lost Soul character and I could see the missing block.  So I went and looked at it, and sure enough, it was a stairway. 
</p>
<p>
Well, that's fine.  I step on it. 
</p>
<p>
'You enter a trap detected zone.  There is a down staircase here.' 
</p>
<p>
I step off it in any direction and I enter a non-trap-detected zone.  So apparently the staircase took its own little bit of the trap-detected zone along with it when it teleported.  Almost reasonable, but extremely silly-looking. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Oh, now that's funny! 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: What exactly is the bug here? 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: I may be missing something here, but I think it's that the trap-detection travels along with the moved staircase. I haven't the faintest whether that'd be a bug or not, but it is amusing. 
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


